* ============================================================
* MCC_EXHAUSTIVE_CORE_REGRESSION_CANARIES.DTS
*
* Exhaustive CORE regression for DotTalk++.
* - Exercises all core subsystems shown in your runs.
* - Includes CANARIES for known fragile/buggy behaviors.
*
* RULES (per your notes):
* - CALC comparisons (= <> <= >= < >) must be wrapped in parentheses.
* - Hyphenated CTOD dates must be quoted.
* - Only TUP is table-buffer aware for display purposes.
*   LIST/SMARTLIST/browsers display actual DBF data.
* - Quotes required for values with spaces; optional otherwise.
* - Some commands may restore cursor; we probe RECNO before/after.
* - TOP/BOTTOM/SKIP are order-aware (physical/CNX/INX). Current ORDER is your clue.
*
* ASCII ONLY.
* Use '*' for inline comments to end-of-line.
* ============================================================

SET ECHO ON
ECHO ===== EXHAUSTIVE CORE REGRESSION START =====
COLOR DEFAULT

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== BASELINE: HELP ROUTER / PRED HELP / BETA CHECK =====
HELP
HELP /PRED
HELP BETA

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== PATHS / ROOTS (if SETPATH exists) =====
SETPATH
SETPATH RESET
SETPATH

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== SCHEMAS: OPEN/CLOSE FULL DBF SET =====
SCHEMAS
SCHEMAS CLOSE
SCHEMAS OPEN DBF
SCHEMAS

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== CLOCK / DATE-TIME (no DBF required) =====
CALC DATE()
CALC TODAY()
CALC TIME()
CALC NOW()
CALC DATETIME()
CALC (DATE() = TODAY())
CALC (NOW() = DATETIME())

ECHO ===== DATE ARITHMETIC CANARIES (known compare/coercion fragility) =====
CALC DATE() + 2
CALC DATE() - 2
ECHO [CANARY] Expected .T. If .F., date compare/coercion regressed:
CALC ((DATE() + 2) > DATE())
ECHO [CANARY] Expected .T. If .F., date compare/coercion regressed:
CALC ((DATE() - 2) < DATE())

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== CTOD / DTOC CANARIES =====
ECHO [CANARY] Unquoted hyphenated date (tokenization canary):
CALC CTOD(2000-01-01)
ECHO [EXPECTED] Quoted hyphenated date:
CALC CTOD("2000-01-01")
ECHO [EXPECTED] Slashed date:
CALC CTOD("2000/01/01")
ECHO [EXPECTED] Numeric yyyymmdd:
CALC CTOD(20000101)

ECHO [SANITY] Date-to-date equality should be .T.:
CALC (CTOD("2000-01-01") = CTOD("2000/01/01"))
CALC (CTOD("2000-01-01") = CTOD(20000101))

ECHO [CANARY] Date + 1 equality expected .T. (was seen failing as .F.):
CALC (CTOD("2000-01-01") + 1 = CTOD("2000-01-02"))
ECHO [CANARY] Date - 1 equality expected .T. (was seen failing as .F.):
CALC (CTOD("2000-01-01") - 1 = CTOD("1999-12-31"))

ECHO [CANARY] DTOC round-trip expected stable string compare:
CALC DTOC(CTOD("2000-01-01"))
CALC (DTOC(CTOD("2000-01-01")) = "20000101")

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== CALC: NUMERIC / PRECEDENCE / COMPARISON RULE =====
CALC 1
CALC 1 + 2
CALC 10 - 3
CALC 6 * 7
CALC 8 / 2
CALC (1 + 2) * 3
CALC 1 + 2 * 3
CALC 0 - 5
CALC -5 + 2
CALC 1 + -2
CALC (1 = 1)
CALC (1 < 2)
CALC (2 > 1)
CALC (2 >= 2)
CALC (2 <= 2)
CALC NOT (1 = 2)
CALC ((1 = 1) AND (2 = 2))
CALC ((1 = 1) OR (1 = 2))

ECHO ===== RHS EXPRESSION CANARIES (you called these out) =====
ECHO [CANARY] RHS arithmetic inside equality (expected .T.):
CALC (3 = 1 + 2)
ECHO [CANARY] Both sides expressions (expected .T.):
CALC ((1 + 2) = (6 / 2))
ECHO [CANARY] Nested compare (expected .T.):
CALC ((1 + 2 * 3) = (1 + (2 * 3)))

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== CALC: STRING BUILTINS ON LITERALS (broad sweep) =====
CALC UPPER("aBc")
CALC LOWER("aBc")
CALC PROPER("joHN")
CALC LEFT("ABCDE", 3)
CALC RIGHT("ABCDE", 2)
CALC ALLTRIM("  hi  ")
CALC LTRIM("  hi  ")
CALC RTRIM("  hi  ")
CALC LEN("ABCDE")
CALC SUBSTR("ABCDE", 2, 3)
CALC AT("CD", "ABCDE")
CALC REPLICATE("x", 5)
CALC SPACE(3)

ECHO [CANARY] TRIM semantics (if TRIM behaves like RTRIM only, equality fails):
CALC TRIM("  hi  ")
CALC (TRIM("  hi  ") = "hi")

ECHO [CANARY] RAT may be missing/unimplemented:
CALC RAT("A", "BANANA")

ECHO ===== QUOTING RULES CANARY (spaces require quotes) =====
CALC (ALLTRIM("a b") = "a b")
CALC (ALLTRIM("  a b  ") = "a b")

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== TABLE SWEEP: OPEN TABLES, STRUCT, COUNT, LIST, TUP, NAV =====
ECHO [NOTE] We touch every shipped MCC table opened by SCHEMAS OPEN DBF.

* ------------- BUILDING -------------
ECHO ===== TABLE: BUILDING =====
SELECT BUILDING
AREA
STRUCT
COUNT
ECHO [PROBE] RECNO before LIST:
RECNO
LIST 3
ECHO [PROBE] RECNO after LIST (cursor-restore probe):
RECNO
TUP
TOP
RECNO
SKIP 1
RECNO
BOTTOM
RECNO
TOP
RECNO

