* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== LOCATE / FIND / SEEK (order-aware, cursor probes) =====
SELECT STUDENTS
TOP
RECNO
LOCATE FOR LNAME = DAVIS
RECNO
TUP
TOP
RECNO
LOCATE FOR LNAME = TAYLOR
RECNO
TUP
TOP
RECNO
FIND LNAME = TAYLOR
RECNO
TOP
RECNO
FIND LNAME = "WHITE"
RECNO
TOP
RECNO
SEEK LNAME = DAVIS
RECNO
TUP
TOP
RECNO
SEEK FNAME = ALEX
RECNO
TUP

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== BOOLEAN / PREDICATE GRAMMAR (field compares) =====
SELECT STUDENTS
LOCATE FOR LNAME = TAYLOR
LIST 1
TUP GPA
BOOLEAN GPA > 3
BOOLEAN GPA < 3
BOOLEAN GPA >= 2 AND GPA <= 4

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== CALC TUPLE: STRING BUILTINS ON LIVE FIELDS =====
SELECT STUDENTS
LOCATE FOR LNAME = TAYLOR
LIST 1
CALC TUPLE UPPER(LNAME)
CALC TUPLE LOWER(LNAME)
CALC TUPLE PROPER(LNAME)
CALC TUPLE LEFT(LNAME, 3)
CALC TUPLE RIGHT(FNAME, 2)
CALC TUPLE ALLTRIM(EMAIL)

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== STUDENTS: DATE FIELDS + DATE ALGEBRA =====
SELECT STUDENTS
LOCATE FOR LNAME = TAYLOR
TUP DOB
TUP ENROLL_D
CALC DOB
CALC DOB + 1
CALC DOB - 1
CALC DATEADD(DOB, 30)
CALC DATEADD(DOB, -30)
CALC DATE() + 30
CALC DATE() - 30
CALC DATEDIFF(DATE(), DOB)
CALC DATE() - DOB
ECHO [CANARY] DATEDIFF vs DATE()-DOB should match as integers:
CALC (DATEDIFF(DATE(), DOB) = (DATE() - DOB))

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== TABLE BUFFER: VISIBILITY + COMMIT (TUP vs LIST) =====
ECHO [RULE] TUP is buffer-aware; LIST shows actual DBF data.

SELECT STUDENTS
LOCATE FOR LNAME = TAYLOR
ECHO [BASELINE] Real DBF (LIST) vs buffer-aware (TUP):
LIST 1
TUP

ECHO [STEP] TABLE ON then change FNAME, verify TUP shows change but LIST does not (until COMMIT).
TABLE ON
REPLACE FNAME WITH "DeraldNew"
ECHO [CANARY] TUP should show DeraldNew immediately:
TUP
ECHO [CANARY] LIST should still show old DBF value if buffering is active:
LIST 1

ECHO [PROBE] Record identity before COMMIT:
RECNO
TUP SID

ECHO [STEP] COMMIT (should preserve record identity):
COMMIT
ECHO [CANARY] Record identity after COMMIT should still be same SID:
RECNO
TUP SID
TUP
ECHO [SANITY] LIST should now reflect new DBF value:
LIST 1

ECHO [STEP] Restore original value (reversible run):
TABLE ON
REPLACE FNAME WITH "Derald"
COMMIT
LIST 1
TUP

ECHO [STEP] TABLE OFF direct write semantics: LIST should reflect immediately after REPLACE.
TABLE OFF
REPLACE FNAME WITH "DeraldZ"
ECHO [SANITY] With TABLE OFF, LIST should show DeraldZ immediately:
LIST 1
TUP
REPLACE FNAME WITH "Derald"
ECHO [SANITY] Restored:
LIST 1
TUP

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== CALCWRITE: REVERSIBLE FIELD WRITE (GPA += .01 then -= .01) =====
ECHO [NOTE] CALCWRITE is triggered by assignment form:
ECHO        CALC GPA = GPA + 0.01
ECHO        Verify with TUP (buffer-aware) and LIST (real DBF depending on TABLE mode).

SELECT STUDENTS
LOCATE FOR LNAME = TAYLOR
TABLE ON
TUP GPA
CALC GPA = GPA + 0.01
ECHO [CANARY] TUP should reflect new GPA (buffer-aware):
TUP GPA
ECHO [CANARY] LIST should still show old GPA until COMMIT if buffering is working:
LIST 1
COMMIT
ECHO [SANITY] After COMMIT, LIST should show updated GPA:
LIST 1
TUP GPA
CALC GPA = GPA - 0.01
COMMIT
ECHO [SANITY] Restored:
LIST 1
TUP GPA

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== TABLE: STALE/FRESH STATUS (if supported) =====
ECHO [NOTE] These are UX/state probes. If your grammar differs, adjust tokens.
SELECT STUDENTS
TABLE ON
REPLACE GENDER WITH "X"
TABLE STALE
TABLE FRESH
COMMIT
TABLE STALE
TABLE OFF

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== COLOR / ECHO SANITY =====
COLOR GREEN
COLOR AMBER
COLOR DEFAULT
SET ECHO OFF
ECHO ===== ECHO OFF CONFIRM =====
SET ECHO ON
ECHO ===== ECHO ON CONFIRM =====

* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO ===== CLEAN SHUTDOWN =====
SCHEMAS
SCHEMAS CLOSE
ECHO ===== EXHAUSTIVE CORE REGRESSION END =====
QUIT
